text: Franklin County is a county found in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2020 census, 7,675 people lived there. Its county seat is Meadville. The county was founded on December 21, 1809 and named for Founding Father Benjamin Franklin. == References == Category:1800s establishments in Mississippi Territory Category:1809 establishments in the United States Category:Mississippi counties
title: Franklin County, Mississippi
